  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, top, tail and slice <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>radishes</strong> as finely as you can</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining radishes</strong> into quarters</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, the juice of the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> king prawns</strong> and <strong>edamame beans</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>remaining toasted sesame oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice has cooked, add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>sesame seed rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-sesame-prawn-and-radish-bowl/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sesame seed</strong> <strong>rice</strong> in bowls with the <strong>radishes</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>king prawns</strong> and <strong>edamame beans</strong> over the top</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>dressing</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining black sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
